            "content": "Standard Manufacturer Warranties: All premium coating systems come with comprehensive manufacturer warranties protecting your investment against product defects and premature failure. Acrylic coating systems: 10-year standard warranty covering product performance, waterproofing integrity, and UV resistance. Silicone coating systems: 15-20 year warranty depending on product grade and thickness applied. Elastomeric coating systems: 12-15 year warranty for premium formulations. These warranties cover coating delamination or peeling from proper substrate, loss of waterproofing allowing leaks, premature degradation from UV exposure, cracking or splitting not caused by substrate movement, and manufacturing defects in coating product.\n\nExtended & Premium Warranties: Many manufacturers offer extended warranties for premium products applied at increased thickness or on ideal substrates. Extended silicone warranties up to 25 years are available for commercial-grade products applied in residential applications at increased mil thickness (25+ mils vs. standard 20 mils). Enhanced acrylic warranties extending to 12-15 years when applied over well-prepared substrates with proper primer systems. System warranties covering complete roof assembly when multiple manufacturer products (primer, coating, sealants) are used together. To qualify for manufacturer warranties, coating must be applied by certified applicators (like our team), at specified minimum thickness (verified by measurements), over approved substrate types in good condition, following manufacturer application procedures, and with proper documentation and registration.\n\nWarranty Exclusions & Limitations: Understanding warranty exclusions protects against surprises. Standard exclusions include damage from Acts of God (hurricanes, tornados, hail exceeding specified size), building structural failures affecting coating, damage from roof traffic or equipment installation, alterations by non-certified contractors, lack of required maintenance per manufacturer guidelines, substrate failures pre-existing at application, and failure to register warranty within specified timeframe. We provide complete warranty documentation at project completion including manufacturer warranty certificate, application details and thickness measurements, maintenance requirements and schedule, registration information and deadlines, and contact information for warranty claims. This documentation is critical for warranty enforcement—keep it with your home records and provide to future owners if selling."
