            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Initial Consultation & Assessment (Day 1, 1-2 hours): Your coating project begins with comprehensive roof assessment by our certified specialists. We'll schedule convenient time for thorough roof inspection examining substrate condition, measuring roof dimensions and calculating square footage, identifying necessary repairs and preparation requirements, testing substrate for coating compatibility, photographing roof condition for documentation and proposal, and assessing drainage patterns and ponding areas. During assessment, we discuss your goals including energy savings priorities, budget considerations, timeline requirements, and aesthetic preferences. We provide honest evaluation of coating suitability versus replacement options. Assessment is completely free with no obligation—we want you fully informed before making any decision.\n\nDetailed Proposal & Quote (Days 2-3): Within 24-48 hours of assessment, we provide comprehensive written proposal including detailed scope of work describing all preparation, repairs, and coating application steps, coating system recommendation with specific products specified, itemized pricing breaking down materials, labor, and any repairs, expected energy savings and ROI analysis, project timeline with estimated start and completion dates, and warranty information for both manufacturer and workmanship coverage. Proposal is transparent with no hidden fees or surprise charges. We schedule follow-up consultation to review proposal, answer questions, and discuss any adjustments. We take time to ensure you understand the investment, value, and expected results before moving forward.\n\nProject Scheduling & Preparation (Days 4-14): Once you approve proposal, we schedule project considering weather forecasts (avoiding monsoon period if possible), your availability and preferences for minimal disruption, optimal application conditions for coating type selected, and current project workload ensuring proper attention to your job. We confirm schedule 48-72 hours before start date and again 24 hours prior. We coordinate any required permitting (rare for coating, more common for structural repairs), order coating materials ensuring fresh product with optimal shelf life, and assign dedicated project manager as your single point of contact. Pre-project communication includes arrival time and technician information, parking and access requirements, any preparation homeowner should complete (removing roof-mounted items if possible), and weather contingency plans.\n\nSurface Preparation & Repairs (Days 1-3 of project): Actual coating work begins with critical preparation phase. Our team arrives on schedule with all necessary equipment and materials, establishes safety perimeter and protects landscaping/property, power washes entire roof surface removing all dirt, debris, and biological growth, and allows minimum 48-hour drying time (weather dependent). During drying period, we complete all identified repairs including patching holes or damaged areas, replacing missing or broken shingles/tiles, repairing or replacing damaged flashing, sealing penetrations and vulnerable areas, and reinforcing stress points with appropriate materials. All repairs must cure completely before coating application. This preparation phase is critical—rushing ruins coating performance. We maintain daily communication updating progress and any discoveries requiring attention.\n\nCoating Application (Days 4-7 of project): With proper preparation complete and substrate dry, coating application proceeds systematically. Day 1: Apply primer coat if required (not all substrates need primer), allow proper cure time per manufacturer specifications (4-24 hours depending on product). Day 2-3: Apply first coating layer at specified wet film thickness (10-15 mils typical), embed reinforcing fabric in wet coating at all seams, penetrations, and transitions, achieve uniform coverage with no missed areas or thin spots, and allow proper cure time (typically 24-48 hours depending on coating type and weather). Day 3-5: Apply second coating layer achieving specified total dry film thickness (typically 18-25 mils for complete system), ensure complete coverage with attention to detail areas, maintain quality throughout application, and allow final cure time before inspection. Weather monitoring throughout ensures we don't apply coating when rain forecast within 24-48 hours or when temperatures are outside optimal range. Unexpected weather can extend timeline—we prioritize proper application over rushed completion.\n\nFinal Inspection & Documentation (Final day): Project completion includes thorough final inspection where we conduct quality walk-through examining all detail work, measure coating thickness at multiple locations verifying specification compliance, photograph completed project showing uniform appearance and coverage, and verify all cleanup completed with debris removed. We provide homeowner walkthrough explaining coating care and maintenance, reviewing warranty coverage and registration, providing all documentation including thickness measurements, warranty certificates, and maintenance guidelines, and answering any final questions. We schedule follow-up contact (30 days) ensuring complete satisfaction and addressing any concerns. Total project timeline: 7-14 days from assessment to completion depending on roof size, complexity, weather delays, and repair requirements. Most 2,000 sq ft homes complete in 8-10 days with optimal conditions. Our ServiceTitan system provides real-time project updates via text/email keeping you informed throughout process."
